Two people have have been killed and seven others injured in an attack at Salima village, Marsabit county. County commissioner Gilbert Kitiyo yesterday said the attackers, who appeared to be on a revenge mission, were searching for weapons stolen from them last month. He said the attackers are suspected to be from a neighbouring community. tension Kitiyo said he could not divulge more details, adding police officers, had been deployed on the ground. It is suspected the attackers run away towards Ngurunit area. No livestock was stolen. Residents have urged security agencies to be vigilant to avert further attacks. “There is tension here, the attackers might come back at any time. We urge the government to beef up security in this region,” a resident, who remained anonymous, said. The incident comes three days after three members of a family were killed during a clash between two communities. Click here for the latest political news